messages.content: "ComfyUI-SD3LatentSelectRes" is a custom node in ComfyUI that allows users to select and resolve the latent sizes of an SD3-based model.
You can install "ComfyUI-SD3LatentSelectRes" by cloning the repository `git clone https://github.com/GavChap/ComfyUI-SD3LatentSelectRes .`
What are the available latent sizes options in "ComfyUI-SD3LatentSelectRes"?
The specific latent sizes options are not mentioned in the document provided, but users can pick the x and y sizes from a list.
What is the size shown in the example image in "ComfyUI-SD3LatentSelectRes"?
Based on the image provided in the link, the size shown appears to be 128x128.
How can one borrow sizes from humblemikey?
The sizes borrowed from humblemikey are not detailed in the document, but it might imply that the content from humblemikey's work has been integrated into this custom node.
